1
00:00:51,650 --> 00:00:52,918
"Dear Amelia:

2
00:00:52,951 --> 00:00:55,420
"Reading your column
has assured me I'm not alone.

3
00:00:55,454 --> 00:00:56,555
"It gets me through the day.

4
00:00:56,588 --> 00:00:59,758
"But at night,
when I try to close my eyes,

5
00:00:59,791 --> 00:01:01,827
"the fear consumes me.

6
00:01:01,860 --> 00:01:03,662
"How do I end this?

7
00:01:03,695 --> 00:01:06,064
"Signed, Embarrassed."

8
00:01:30,088 --> 00:01:31,723
- "Dear Embarrassed:

9
00:01:31,757 --> 00:01:35,093
"I admire your courage
and pray for your safety.

10
00:01:36,695 --> 00:01:39,665
"You must find a way to
leave someway, somehow.

11
00:01:39,698 --> 00:01:42,100
"Surviving is the start
of your journey.

12
00:01:42,134 --> 00:01:45,537
"Living is the finish line.
Never back down."

13
00:01:46,838 --> 00:01:48,407
"Dear Amelia:

14
00:01:48,440 --> 00:01:50,842
"Your words continue
to give me strength.

15
00:01:50,876 --> 00:01:53,712
"I need to get out,
but feel trapped.

16
00:01:53,745 --> 00:01:55,947
"Signed, Embarrassed."

17
00:01:58,417 --> 00:02:01,720
- "Dear Embarrassed:
My heart goes out to you.

18
00:02:01,753 --> 00:02:04,990
"I know how hard it is, but
you must go to the police.

19
00:02:06,458 --> 00:02:10,128
"There are support systems
in place to help you.

20
00:02:10,162 --> 00:02:13,565
"Your husband should never
lay a hand on you again."

21
00:02:14,933 --> 00:02:18,570
- "Dear Amelia: Going to
the police is too dangerous.

22
00:02:18,603 --> 00:02:20,505
"What do I do to stop this?"

23
00:02:23,475 --> 00:02:24,876
- "Dear Embarrassed:

24
00:02:24,910 --> 00:02:28,580
"The answer to your question
is both simple and difficult:

25
00:02:28,613 --> 00:02:30,449
"Whatever it takes."

26
00:02:31,483 --> 00:02:32,851
- What are you doing?

27
00:02:41,660 --> 00:02:43,762
I don't believe this.

28
00:02:43,795 --> 00:02:46,098
It doesn't matter
what I do.

29
00:02:46,131 --> 00:02:48,967
You just keep pushing me
and pushing me

30
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,769
to do things that
I don't wanna do.

31
00:02:50,802 --> 00:02:53,038
- You can't do this.
It's not right.

32
00:02:53,071 --> 00:02:54,740
- Don't you
tell me what's right!

33
00:02:54,773 --> 00:02:56,775
- What are you doing?
Threatening me?

34
00:02:56,808 --> 00:02:58,977
- I'm done making threats.

35
00:02:59,010 --> 00:03:01,012
- What's that
supposed to mean?

36
00:03:03,548 --> 00:03:05,717
Put it down, Trevor.

37
00:03:09,187 --> 00:03:12,057
Put it down, Trevor.
Put it down.

38
00:03:12,090 --> 00:03:14,426
- What are you
gonna do about it?

39
00:03:25,971 --> 00:03:28,807
- Sometimes, when we go through
a traumatic experience,

40
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:33,512
the fears that linger are
undetectable, even to ourselves.

41
00:03:33,545 --> 00:03:35,213
And we need
to take a step back

42
00:03:35,247 --> 00:03:37,616
and remember what
it was like before.

43
00:03:37,649 --> 00:03:39,651
Who we were before.

44
00:03:39,684 --> 00:03:43,922
Before you lost your job,
before the death in the family,

45
00:03:43,955 --> 00:03:46,925
before you caught
him cheating,

46
00:03:46,958 --> 00:03:48,727
before the violence.

47
00:03:49,795 --> 00:03:51,997
I wanna thank
all of you for coming.

48
00:03:52,030 --> 00:03:55,267
It gives me hope knowing
that our shared experiences

49
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,635
can bring strength.

50
00:03:56,668 --> 00:03:58,770
We learn from our past,

51
00:03:58,804 --> 00:04:01,239
we refuse to let it
define our present

52
00:04:01,273 --> 00:04:03,108
and we build
our own future.

53
00:04:03,141 --> 00:04:06,645
Never back down.
Thank you.

54
00:04:15,620 --> 00:04:18,824
- I just wanna
say thank you.

55
00:04:18,857 --> 00:04:21,860
Your column guided
me through the worst.

56
00:04:21,893 --> 00:04:24,296
And you're my touchstone
every morning.

57
00:04:24,329 --> 00:04:26,865
- Thank you.
It works both ways.

58
00:04:26,898 --> 00:04:29,000
Your appreciation
gives me my strength.

59
00:04:30,001 --> 00:04:31,736
- You should write a book.

60
00:04:31,770 --> 00:04:34,005
- Actually,
I just started a blog.

61
00:04:34,039 --> 00:04:35,574
It's called
Never Back Down.

62
00:04:35,607 --> 00:04:36,575
You know, it'd be great

63
00:04:36,608 --> 00:04:39,010
to have some more
strong voices on the site.

64
00:04:39,044 --> 00:04:40,045
- Count me in.

65
00:04:40,078 --> 00:04:42,948
- The link's on the bottom.
What's your name?

66
00:04:42,981 --> 00:04:44,249
- Jenny Reardon.

67
00:04:44,282 --> 00:04:45,750
- It's nice to meet you.

68
00:04:45,784 --> 00:04:47,018
- Hi, nice to meet you.

69
00:04:47,052 --> 00:04:50,989
There's just something else
I need to tell you.

70
00:04:51,022 --> 00:04:53,291
Um, I'm Embarrassed.

71
00:04:53,325 --> 00:04:56,127
- Please don't be.
I'm here to listen.

72
00:04:56,161 --> 00:04:59,531
- No. I'm Embarrassed.

73
00:05:02,667 --> 00:05:04,302
- My God!

74
00:05:23,154 --> 00:05:24,990
- To the cover girl.

75
00:05:25,023 --> 00:05:26,992
- It's no big deal.

76
00:05:27,025 --> 00:05:29,995
- Yes, it is. This is what
you've been working for.

77
00:05:30,028 --> 00:05:31,930
- What we've
been working for.

78
00:05:31,963 --> 00:05:34,866
- I think we need to
capitalize on the attention.

79
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:37,302
I know you're busy with
your speaking gigs,

80
00:05:37,335 --> 00:05:39,838
but the blog is
your future. Look.

81
00:05:43,975 --> 00:05:46,211
Here is a list
of email addresses

82
00:05:46,244 --> 00:05:48,079
who have created
a member profile.

83
00:05:48,113 --> 00:05:51,616
And here is a list of people
who have actively posted.

84
00:05:51,650 --> 00:05:54,653
It's 92%. That's unheard of
in this industry.

85
00:05:54,686 --> 00:05:57,756
The problem is nobody else
knows it exists.

86
00:05:58,757 --> 00:05:59,991
- I'm not sure
the newspaper

87
00:06:00,025 --> 00:06:02,360
would want me to drive
people away from my column.

88
00:06:02,394 --> 00:06:03,795
- Well, screw
the
Sentinel.

89
00:06:03,828 --> 00:06:05,697
Nobody wants to
get ink on their hands.

90
00:06:05,730 --> 00:06:08,233
I can get you primo placement
on the search engines.

91
00:06:08,266 --> 00:06:09,701
- For a shoestring budget?

92
00:06:09,734 --> 00:06:10,936
- Don't get me wrong.

93
00:06:10,969 --> 00:06:13,004
If you gave me $2 million,
I could spend it.

94
00:06:13,038 --> 00:06:16,074
I could spend it better than any
other search-engine optimizer,

95
00:06:16,107 --> 00:06:18,810
and I'd still get you better
placement on a Web search.

96
00:06:18,843 --> 00:06:22,113
A few structural tweaks
on your site,

97
00:06:22,147 --> 00:06:24,115
maximize keyword density...

98
00:06:26,284 --> 00:06:30,722
OK, bottom line is, if anybody
needs help or advice,

99
00:06:30,755 --> 00:06:34,392
the first site they will
see is
Never Back Down.

100
00:06:34,426 --> 00:06:36,995
All you have to do
is give me the go-ahead.

101
00:06:37,028 --> 00:06:39,664
What do you have to lose?

102
00:06:43,034 --> 00:06:44,669
- All right, let's do it.

103
00:06:45,770 --> 00:06:46,771
- Yes!

104
00:06:51,042 --> 00:06:53,011
- It is pretty cool.

105
00:07:03,288 --> 00:07:05,290
- I'm up for that.

106
00:07:07,459 --> 00:07:09,427
- Thank you.

107
00:07:10,428 --> 00:07:12,864
- Thanks.

108
00:07:12,897 --> 00:07:14,299
- To you.

109
00:07:23,174 --> 00:07:26,711
- Hottie at 9:00
is checking you out.

110
00:07:26,745 --> 00:07:28,713
- I doubt it.

111
00:07:34,886 --> 00:07:35,854
My God!

112
00:07:35,887 --> 00:07:36,855
- I told you.

113
00:07:36,888 --> 00:07:38,456
- You made me look there.

114
00:07:38,490 --> 00:07:41,926
- Well, who says that you
should meet new people

115
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:44,396
and not shut yourself off
from relationships?

116
00:07:44,429 --> 00:07:46,064
That's right. You.

117
00:07:46,097 --> 00:07:47,165
- OK.

118
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:51,202
- Meeting guys in a bar,
it's never a good idea.

119
00:07:51,236 --> 00:07:53,038
- And you met Darryl
at a bookstore

120
00:07:53,071 --> 00:07:54,906
in the home-and-
garden section.

121
00:07:54,939 --> 00:07:56,207
- Good point.

122
00:07:56,241 --> 00:07:58,810
- I'm sorry. I didn't
mean to say that.

123
00:07:58,843 --> 00:08:00,945
I shouldn't
have said that.

124
00:08:00,979 --> 00:08:03,815
- Darryl? Forget it.

125
00:08:03,848 --> 00:08:06,317
He's locked up
for 2 more years.

126
00:08:08,486 --> 00:08:11,122
- Ooh, he's coming over.

127
00:08:11,156 --> 00:08:13,925
You'd better
get ready, girl.

128
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:15,093
- My gosh!

129
00:08:21,099 --> 00:08:22,934
- I'm sorry
to bother you,

130
00:08:22,967 --> 00:08:26,104
but I noticed you
looking my way and laughing.

131
00:08:28,273 --> 00:08:30,375
I couldn't help but
find out what's so funny.

132
00:08:30,408 --> 00:08:33,978
- I don't remember
talking about him, do you?

133
00:08:34,012 --> 00:08:36,481
- We were talking
about gardening.

134
00:08:36,514 --> 00:08:40,051
- I know what you said.
I can read lips.

135
00:08:40,085 --> 00:08:41,820
- You're bluffing.

136
00:08:41,853 --> 00:08:43,288
- Your name is Amelia.

137
00:08:51,296 --> 00:08:52,864
That's a pretty
good trick.

138
00:08:52,897 --> 00:08:56,000
- I've got another one.
All I need is your phone number.

139
00:08:56,034 --> 00:08:58,403
- Nice try,
but I'm not in the habit

140
00:08:58,436 --> 00:09:00,238
of giving
my phone number out

141
00:09:00,271 --> 00:09:02,874
to a guy I've just met
for the first time.

142
00:09:02,907 --> 00:09:05,810
- Do you know what every great
love story has in common?

143
00:09:05,844 --> 00:09:07,479
- No, what?

144
00:09:07,512 --> 00:09:10,815
- At one point, they also
met for the first time.

145
00:09:41,212 --> 00:09:42,847
- Thank you for coming.

146
00:09:42,881 --> 00:09:44,849
I look forward to hearing

147
00:09:44,883 --> 00:09:47,051
from each and every one
of you online.

148
00:09:47,085 --> 00:09:48,353
It gives me hope knowing

149
00:09:48,386 --> 00:09:51,222
that our shared experiences
can bring strength.

150
00:09:52,223 --> 00:09:54,459
We learn from our past,

151
00:09:54,492 --> 00:09:56,861
we refuse to let it
define our present

152
00:09:56,895 --> 00:09:58,596
and we build
our own future.

153
00:09:58,630 --> 00:10:01,032
And as always,
never back down.

154
00:10:02,033 --> 00:10:03,301
Thank you.

155
00:10:07,305 --> 00:10:09,040
Bravo!

156
00:10:10,108 --> 00:10:12,076
Thank you.

157
00:10:18,049 --> 00:10:19,484
- Thank you for coming.

158
00:10:23,621 --> 00:10:25,123
Thank you.

159
00:10:30,395 --> 00:10:32,197
Thank you. Hi!

160
00:10:32,230 --> 00:10:33,198
- Hi.

161
00:10:33,231 --> 00:10:34,632
- Were you here
the whole time?

162
00:10:34,666 --> 00:10:38,269
- And loved every minute
of it. Even the Q & A.

163
00:10:38,303 --> 00:10:40,605
They didn't wanna
let you leave.

164
00:10:40,638 --> 00:10:43,408
- I hope you weren't
charging me by the hour.

165
00:10:43,441 --> 00:10:44,909
- Of course not, kiddo.

166
00:10:44,943 --> 00:10:47,612
I take my 5% off the top.

167
00:10:47,645 --> 00:10:51,950
Speaking of which, I have
something big in the works.

168
00:10:51,983 --> 00:10:55,920
- In the works?
As in Modern Media Works?

169
00:10:55,954 --> 00:10:57,922
- Now, don't
jinx it for us.

170
00:10:57,956 --> 00:10:59,290
Just let me
do my thing.

171
00:10:59,324 --> 00:11:01,059
But when the time
is right,

172
00:11:01,092 --> 00:11:04,462
I'll need you to win over
a tougher crowd.

173
00:11:04,495 --> 00:11:07,198
I have to go, but I'll call
you in the morning, OK?

174
00:11:07,232 --> 00:11:08,533
- OK, thank you.

175
00:11:08,566 --> 00:11:10,134
- Bye.

176
00:11:10,168 --> 00:11:11,603
- Bye.

177
00:11:42,433 --> 00:11:44,002
- Party on
the 15th floor.

178
00:11:44,035 --> 00:11:46,070
They've been
holding it up all day.

179
00:11:47,071 --> 00:11:49,307
We met a while ago
at the bar.

180
00:11:49,340 --> 00:11:50,675
- I remember.

181
00:11:50,708 --> 00:11:53,144
- I've been back there
a couple of times

182
00:11:53,177 --> 00:11:54,445
hoping to see you again.

183
00:11:54,479 --> 00:11:57,315
- I don't have much of
a social life these days.

184
00:11:57,348 --> 00:11:59,183
- I know.
You work too hard.

185
00:11:59,217 --> 00:12:02,487
I found your site.
It posts your event schedule.

186
00:12:05,657 --> 00:12:10,061
- Look, I'm not into
these kinds of games.

187
00:12:10,094 --> 00:12:13,464
- I wanted to see you again,
so here I am. No games.

188
00:12:15,767 --> 00:12:17,735
Listen, probably
not the best idea

189
00:12:17,769 --> 00:12:19,304
showing up here
unannounced,

190
00:12:19,337 --> 00:12:21,606
but that still doesn't
take away from the fact

191
00:12:21,639 --> 00:12:23,274
that I'd like
to take you out.

192
00:12:27,111 --> 00:12:29,380
In case you lost
the first one.

193
00:12:33,084 --> 00:12:34,552
Call me.

194
00:12:40,825 --> 00:12:43,027
- My gosh!
Where have you been?

195
00:12:43,061 --> 00:12:45,296
I've been looking
all over for you.

196
00:12:45,330 --> 00:12:47,465
- I've just been working
the room. Where else?

197
00:12:47,498 --> 00:12:50,034
More importantly, who was
that you were talking to?

198
00:12:50,068 --> 00:12:52,704
- Remember Romeo
from the bar?

199
00:12:52,737 --> 00:12:55,606
- Get out of town!
What happened?

200
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:57,508
- He wants me
to call him.

201
00:12:57,542 --> 00:12:59,310
- So call him.
Set a date.

202
00:12:59,344 --> 00:13:00,611
Go out.
Take charge!

203
00:13:00,645 --> 00:13:02,747
Come on, isn't that
your motto?

204
00:13:02,780 --> 00:13:06,317
- No, dating is the last thing
on my mind right know.

205
00:13:40,818 --> 00:13:44,756
- OK, so you're gonna check in
with me 3 times a day by phone:

206
00:13:44,789 --> 00:13:46,557
9:00 a.m, 3:00 p.m.
and 9:00 p.m.

207
00:13:46,591 --> 00:13:48,626
My number is at the
bottom of the page.

208
00:13:48,659 --> 00:13:50,628
When you check in with me
at nighttime,

209
00:13:50,661 --> 00:13:53,264
that means you're in for
the night, no exceptions.

210
00:13:53,297 --> 00:13:54,399
You got that?

211
00:13:54,432 --> 00:13:56,434
You're gonna start
to look for a job.

212
00:13:56,467 --> 00:13:58,636
If you need assistance
in finding a job,

213
00:13:58,669 --> 00:14:00,338
we have
a placement program.

214
00:14:00,371 --> 00:14:01,839
That's what
we're there for.

215
00:14:01,873 --> 00:14:04,809
Just basically make sure
you stay out of trouble

216
00:14:04,842 --> 00:14:07,178
and keep your nose clean
at all times.

217
00:14:07,211 --> 00:14:09,847
You understand exactly what
I'm telling you, Mr. Devine?

218
00:14:09,881 --> 00:14:11,449
Is it clear?

219
00:14:11,482 --> 00:14:13,484
- Perfectly.

220
00:14:15,353 --> 00:14:17,155
- There you go.

221
00:15:36,734 --> 00:15:38,402
- Ciao, this is Carlo Rossi.

222
00:15:38,436 --> 00:15:40,771
Please leave me
a message after the tone.

223
00:15:40,805 --> 00:15:44,842
- Hi, this is Amelia from
the bar and the conference.

224
00:15:44,876 --> 00:15:47,678
Um, how about dinner
tomorrow night?

225
00:15:47,712 --> 00:15:50,882
- I know a little place
in Beacon Hill. -00?

226
00:15:50,915 --> 00:15:53,551
Let me know
if that works for you.

227
00:15:53,584 --> 00:15:58,589
My number is 202 555-0152.

228
00:16:15,473 --> 00:16:17,208
- Detective Wilson.

229
00:16:21,746 --> 00:16:23,548
- You keep telling me
to call you Hank

230
00:16:23,581 --> 00:16:25,716
and then you call yourself
Detective Wilson.

231
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:27,718
- Hey, I never know
who's behind the door.

232
00:16:28,886 --> 00:16:30,988
- This is
a pleasant surprise.

233
00:16:31,022 --> 00:16:31,989
How's the family?

234
00:16:32,023 --> 00:16:33,391
- They're great.

235
00:16:33,424 --> 00:16:34,992
Our youngest one
is off to college

236
00:16:35,026 --> 00:16:36,227
at the end of summer.

237
00:16:36,260 --> 00:16:39,363
I'm hoping to spend a couple of
weeks with him up at the lake,

238
00:16:39,397 --> 00:16:40,965
but you know,
with all the work...

239
00:16:40,998 --> 00:16:43,434
- Still putting in
14-hour days?

240
00:16:44,602 --> 00:16:46,804
- Please give
my regards to Cindy.

241
00:16:46,837 --> 00:16:48,372
- Will do.

242
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:51,842
- What's the matter, Hank?

243
00:16:52,877 --> 00:16:55,513
- I wish I had
better news for you, Amelia.

244
00:16:56,514 --> 00:16:57,915
Darryl's been released.

245
00:16:57,949 --> 00:16:59,584
- When?

246
00:16:59,617 --> 00:17:00,885
- Last Thursday.

247
00:17:00,918 --> 00:17:03,588
Paperwork just
got on my desk today.

248
00:17:03,621 --> 00:17:05,256
I came straight over.

249
00:17:16,367 --> 00:17:20,037
- I know this isn't your fault,
but how is this possible?

250
00:17:20,071 --> 00:17:21,772
- State's broke.

251
00:17:21,806 --> 00:17:24,609
I've been in domestic abuse
for over 20 years,

252
00:17:24,642 --> 00:17:26,944
and this is the worst
I've ever seen it.

253
00:17:28,045 --> 00:17:30,314
All the cutbacks,
overcrowding.

254
00:17:30,348 --> 00:17:32,550
And for some reason,
domestic-abuse offenders

255
00:17:32,583 --> 00:17:35,553
are the first ones to receive
a get-out-of-jail-free card.

256
00:17:35,586 --> 00:17:38,489
- Great, so how am I
supposed to feel safe?

257
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:46,530
- Look, I made sure the
restraining order was in effect.

258
00:17:46,564 --> 00:17:48,032
- What?

259
00:17:48,065 --> 00:17:50,801
- One slip-up on his part
and he's right back in prison.

260
00:17:50,835 --> 00:17:52,837
- That's if you
can catch him.

261
00:17:54,005 --> 00:17:57,541
You can't protect
me 24/7, Hank.

262
00:17:57,575 --> 00:18:00,478
- I'm gonna be checking in with
his parole officer every day.

263
00:18:01,846 --> 00:18:05,316
Amelia. Amelia!

264
00:18:06,384 --> 00:18:08,986
He's not gonna
hurt you again.

265
00:18:18,996 --> 00:18:21,132
- I have a confession.

266
00:18:21,165 --> 00:18:24,735
I read your blog.
It's fascinating.

267
00:18:24,769 --> 00:18:27,004
So raw and emotional.

268
00:18:27,038 --> 00:18:30,975
- I don't edit my words.
I write what I feel.

269
00:18:31,976 --> 00:18:33,878
And lately, I've been...

270
00:18:33,911 --> 00:18:37,548
- Venting. Sorry,
I didn't mean to...

271
00:18:37,581 --> 00:18:40,951
- No, I'm the one
who should apologize.

272
00:18:40,985 --> 00:18:45,990
It's been a long week, and I'm
not very good company right now.

273
00:18:47,024 --> 00:18:48,826
- You could talk to me.

274
00:18:52,096 --> 00:18:55,866
- My ex-husband Darryl was
just released from prison.

275
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:58,602
Listen, I know that
I invited you, but....

276
00:18:58,636 --> 00:19:00,905
- No, no, please.
I understand.

277
00:19:02,840 --> 00:19:04,008
No, let me.

278
00:19:04,041 --> 00:19:05,609
- I insist.

279
00:19:12,817 --> 00:19:15,619
- You must promise
me 2 things.

280
00:19:15,653 --> 00:19:18,622
Next time, I pay.

281
00:19:18,656 --> 00:19:21,792
And even though
we both have our cars,

282
00:19:21,826 --> 00:19:24,061
you'll let me
see you home.

283
00:19:25,463 --> 00:19:27,631
- I'd appreciate that.

284
00:22:13,163 --> 00:22:18,135
"False starts. One must take
all the time one needs.

285
00:22:18,168 --> 00:22:22,006
"Healing works on its own
schedule, not yours.

286
00:22:22,039 --> 00:22:23,807
"False starts and setbacks

287
00:22:23,841 --> 00:22:26,911
"are part of the
long hard road to recovery."

288
00:22:46,797 --> 00:22:47,998
- Miss Davis,
Miss Frankel,

289
00:22:48,032 --> 00:22:49,833
a pleasure to
finally meet you both.

290
00:22:49,867 --> 00:22:50,868
Colin Grosslight.
- Hi.

291
00:22:50,901 --> 00:22:53,938
- Please follow me.
The team is eager to meet you.

292
00:22:56,373 --> 00:22:58,375
In this business,
there's a small window

293
00:22:58,409 --> 00:22:59,910
to turn a spark
into a flame.

294
00:22:59,944 --> 00:23:01,712
Your audience is small
but growing.

295
00:23:01,745 --> 00:23:04,248
And if you want this to become
more than a niche blog,

296
00:23:04,281 --> 00:23:06,850
you're gonna need our help.

297
00:23:06,884 --> 00:23:09,787
- A niche blog?

298
00:23:09,820 --> 00:23:13,057
Marginalizing Amelia's
audience is condescending

299
00:23:13,090 --> 00:23:16,193
and frankly not the best way
to start off a new partnership.

300
00:23:16,226 --> 00:23:17,361
- That is not our intent.

301
00:23:17,394 --> 00:23:18,963
We know the numbers
are strong

302
00:23:18,996 --> 00:23:20,197
given the circumstances.

303
00:23:20,230 --> 00:23:21,398
And we love the demo.

304
00:23:21,432 --> 00:23:23,867
We wouldn't be
sitting here otherwise.

305
00:23:23,901 --> 00:23:26,136
And the women who read
your blog trust you,

306
00:23:26,170 --> 00:23:27,404
and that is
invaluable to us.

307
00:23:27,438 --> 00:23:29,239
- And to your advertisers.

308
00:23:29,273 --> 00:23:31,875
- We already have
the majors ready to commit.

309
00:23:31,909 --> 00:23:32,943
Just say the word.

310
00:23:32,977 --> 00:23:35,145
- Slow down.
What about content?

311
00:23:35,179 --> 00:23:37,381
- We don't care
what you write

312
00:23:37,414 --> 00:23:38,882
as long as people
are reading.

313
00:23:38,916 --> 00:23:40,417
- And clicking
every now and then.

314
00:23:45,923 --> 00:23:47,758
- Jody, right?

315
00:23:47,791 --> 00:23:49,259
- Right.

316
00:23:49,293 --> 00:23:52,296
- I'm guessing you haven't
been vocal in the meeting

317
00:23:52,329 --> 00:23:54,732
because you didn't
work on these mock-ups.

318
00:23:57,935 --> 00:24:01,972
- I reviewed them, but no,
I didn't work on them.

319
00:24:05,042 --> 00:24:08,312
- So she's here because you
think another woman in the room

320
00:24:08,345 --> 00:24:10,314
will make me feel
more comfortable?

321
00:24:10,347 --> 00:24:12,816
- I know
all about your blog.

322
00:24:14,351 --> 00:24:18,789
- You have a small window to
impress a prospective client.

323
00:24:18,822 --> 00:24:20,724
That window
is about to close.

324
00:24:21,959 --> 00:24:24,795
What do you think
of the presentation?

325
00:24:26,497 --> 00:24:29,400
- There's a visual flair
that's familiar,

326
00:24:29,433 --> 00:24:32,136
but it's--it's
missing your imprint.

327
00:24:33,437 --> 00:24:36,740
- I think it's
a Carrie Bradshaw rip-off.

328
00:24:38,909 --> 00:24:41,078
I'll be back next week
to hear your pitch.

329
00:24:45,983 --> 00:24:49,820
And by the way,
it's one butterfly.

330
00:26:55,412 --> 00:26:58,081
- Well, there's no sign
of forced entry.

331
00:26:58,115 --> 00:27:01,218
We'll ask the neighbours
if anyone saw something,

332
00:27:01,251 --> 00:27:03,187
but so far,
we've got nothing.

333
00:27:03,220 --> 00:27:05,589
Have you received any
threatening messages lately?

334
00:27:05,622 --> 00:27:06,957
Maybe on your computer?

335
00:27:06,990 --> 00:27:09,626
- This is obviously Darryl.

336
00:27:09,660 --> 00:27:12,062
- Well, Darryl is
the most likely suspect.

337
00:27:12,095 --> 00:27:14,965
If it is him, we know that
he'll slip up eventually.

338
00:27:14,998 --> 00:27:18,535
But the problem is that you've
become a public figure, Amelia.

339
00:27:18,569 --> 00:27:20,604
And we can't ignore
the possibility

340
00:27:20,637 --> 00:27:23,073
that this attack might
be connected to the blog.

341
00:27:24,107 --> 00:27:26,109
- I highly doubt that.

342
00:27:26,143 --> 00:27:28,545
- Well, obsessed fans,
angry husbands.

343
00:27:28,579 --> 00:27:30,080
I just wanna make sure

344
00:27:30,113 --> 00:27:32,983
that we look into
all the possibilities here.

345
00:27:33,016 --> 00:27:34,585
- So you're
basically telling me

346
00:27:34,618 --> 00:27:37,020
that I have to
be afraid of everybody?

347
00:27:39,990 --> 00:27:42,392
- Is your address
listed anywhere?

348
00:27:42,426 --> 00:27:44,361
- No, I don't
ever give it out.

349
00:27:44,394 --> 00:27:48,198
- What about neighbours? Have
you had any disputes recently?

350
00:27:48,232 --> 00:27:50,534
- I pretty much
keep to myself.

351
00:27:52,703 --> 00:27:55,138
- Is there anyone new
in your life?

352
00:28:06,650 --> 00:28:09,086
- We went on one date.

353
00:28:09,119 --> 00:28:11,688
He seems like
a really nice guy.

354
00:28:11,722 --> 00:28:15,125
I just... I can't imagine that
he would do something like this.

355
00:28:15,158 --> 00:28:17,160
- Well, it won't hurt
to check him out.

356
00:28:17,194 --> 00:28:19,563
And if you don't mind,
I'm gonna have the tech guys

357
00:28:19,596 --> 00:28:22,099
from the station
look into your Web site.

358
00:28:22,132 --> 00:28:23,934
See if that
leads to anything.

359
00:28:24,735 --> 00:28:27,537
Hey, we're gonna
catch this guy.

360
00:28:34,578 --> 00:28:38,115
- You know I'm not gonna answer
a thing without my lawyer.

361
00:28:39,383 --> 00:28:43,186
- Yeah well, the problem with
lawyers is they cost money.

362
00:28:43,220 --> 00:28:45,689
And, um, by the look
of this place,

363
00:28:45,722 --> 00:28:48,959
you'd be best off
talking to me yourself.

364
00:28:52,462 --> 00:28:55,365
- You look old, Detective.

365
00:28:56,366 --> 00:28:57,601
- I'd look even older

366
00:28:57,634 --> 00:29:00,404
if you'd spent the whole
5 years in prison.

367
00:29:01,471 --> 00:29:03,407
- I'm not saying
I was a choir boy,

368
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:05,342
but I didn't deserve
all that time.

369
00:29:05,375 --> 00:29:08,011
And losing Amelia
was enough of a punishment.

370
00:29:11,081 --> 00:29:12,049
- Losing Amelia?

371
00:29:12,082 --> 00:29:13,050
- Yeah.

372
00:29:13,083 --> 00:29:14,685
- And when
exactly was that?

373
00:29:14,718 --> 00:29:16,286
Was that before or after

374
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:18,221
you threw her down
a flight of stairs?

375
00:29:18,255 --> 00:29:20,724
Or maybe it's the time
you put her in the hospital

376
00:29:20,757 --> 00:29:21,658
with your fists.

377
00:29:21,692 --> 00:29:24,161
It's too bad I don't
hand out the sentences.

378
00:29:26,263 --> 00:29:30,400
- Tough guy with your badge
and your piece.

379
00:29:31,702 --> 00:29:33,570
Truth is you couldn't
protect her then.

380
00:29:33,603 --> 00:29:36,306
And from the looks of things,
you can't protect her now.

381
00:29:36,340 --> 00:29:38,775
- I'm watching you, Devine.

382
00:29:38,809 --> 00:29:42,112
I'm watching
every move you make.

383
00:29:42,145 --> 00:29:44,014
- Are we done here?

384
00:30:13,176 --> 00:30:14,711
- Thanks for having me.

385
00:30:15,846 --> 00:30:18,782
I just couldn't stay there
until the alarm was in.

386
00:30:18,815 --> 00:30:21,451
- Don't mention it.
I could use the company.

387
00:30:22,719 --> 00:30:24,554
This'll make it
more comfortable.

388
00:30:24,588 --> 00:30:26,757
- Thanks.

389
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:31,528
- How about some tea?

390
00:30:31,561 --> 00:30:34,364
- Yeah, that'd be
great. Thank you.

391
00:30:38,335 --> 00:30:40,804
Do you think
it was Darryl?

392
00:30:40,837 --> 00:30:43,340
- I don't know
who else it could be.

393
00:30:48,211 --> 00:30:50,747
After he hit me
the first time...

394
00:30:52,516 --> 00:30:54,618
I knew when
it was coming.

395
00:30:55,619 --> 00:30:57,487
When he was drinking...

396
00:30:58,488 --> 00:31:00,424
or when we'd argue.

397
00:31:02,659 --> 00:31:04,828
But this is different.

398
00:31:06,563 --> 00:31:11,101
Not knowing when or
where it might happen again.

399
00:31:12,369 --> 00:31:16,440
But it's like that feeling
in the pit of my stomach

400
00:31:16,473 --> 00:31:17,441
is the same.

401
00:31:17,474 --> 00:31:19,476
Does that
make any sense?

402
00:31:20,510 --> 00:31:21,878
- Yeah.

403
00:31:21,912 --> 00:31:23,880
- And what
bothers me most

404
00:31:23,914 --> 00:31:27,217
is how everything I feel
I've worked so hard for

405
00:31:27,250 --> 00:31:28,885
can be taken away
like that.

406
00:31:31,188 --> 00:31:33,356
- No one can take away
what you've achieved

407
00:31:33,390 --> 00:31:34,724
or the progress
you've made.

408
00:31:38,929 --> 00:31:42,799
- How did you do it?
How did you fight back?

409
00:31:42,833 --> 00:31:45,235
- It was a long road.

410
00:31:45,268 --> 00:31:49,673
Martial arts taught me
some self-confidence, but...

411
00:31:50,874 --> 00:31:53,510
it wasn't until
I started writing you

412
00:31:53,543 --> 00:31:58,215
that I realized there's a
possibility of a better life.

413
00:32:02,652 --> 00:32:05,155
One day, I just snapped.

414
00:32:06,256 --> 00:32:09,426
It didn't feel real
until I saw the blood.

415
00:32:10,427 --> 00:32:11,895
That changed everything.

416
00:32:13,530 --> 00:32:15,599
- I'm not sure
I can do it.

417
00:32:15,632 --> 00:32:17,234
- You fought back.

418
00:32:17,267 --> 00:32:19,970
You did it once and
you can do it again.

419
00:32:20,003 --> 00:32:23,540
We don't even know who
it is that's doing this.

420
00:32:23,573 --> 00:32:26,643
But whoever it is, you're strong
enough to do whatever it takes.

421
00:32:26,676 --> 00:32:28,612
- I'm just not sure

422
00:32:28,645 --> 00:32:32,249
that I have that kind
of courage anymore.

423
00:32:32,282 --> 00:32:34,184
- Neither was I.

424
00:32:35,318 --> 00:32:39,289
But you were there for me.
And now I'm there for you.

425
00:32:40,657 --> 00:32:43,760
- Thanks. I needed that.

426
00:32:53,603 --> 00:32:55,205
- Thanks.

427
00:32:56,006 --> 00:32:58,441
Mr. Rossi.
- Yes?

428
00:32:58,475 --> 00:33:01,278
- I have a few questions for
you. This shouldn't take long.

429
00:33:01,311 --> 00:33:03,980
- Is this about my work visa?
I renewed it through the mail.

430
00:33:04,014 --> 00:33:05,715
- No.

431
00:33:05,749 --> 00:33:08,318
- Well then, what can I
help you with, Officer?

432
00:33:08,351 --> 00:33:09,586
- Actually, it's Detective.

433
00:33:11,021 --> 00:33:13,456
- Please come in.

434
00:33:22,966 --> 00:33:24,935
- I need to know
your whereabouts

435
00:33:24,968 --> 00:33:26,670
this past Wednesday evening.

436
00:33:26,703 --> 00:33:28,438
- Why?

437
00:33:28,471 --> 00:33:31,241
- I'll ask the questions,
Mr. Rossi.

438
00:33:37,080 --> 00:33:39,015
- Wednesday.

439
00:33:40,050 --> 00:33:41,551
I was at Dusty's Bar.

440
00:33:41,585 --> 00:33:43,353
I was meeting
someone at 5:00.

441
00:33:43,386 --> 00:33:45,956
It lasted about an hour.
I stayed after he left.

442
00:33:45,989 --> 00:33:48,491
- You stayed until what time?

443
00:33:48,525 --> 00:33:50,026
Not sure. 10:00 maybe.

444
00:33:50,060 --> 00:33:53,730
- Maybe's are no good for me.
I need you to be sure.

445
00:33:54,764 --> 00:33:56,833
Yes, 10:00.

446
00:33:57,867 --> 00:34:00,036
- And who were you with?

447
00:34:00,070 --> 00:34:02,572
- The meeting was with
some potential clients.

448
00:34:02,606 --> 00:34:04,808
I stayed afterwards
for a burger and a beer.

449
00:34:05,809 --> 00:34:07,510
- You stayed by yourself?

450
00:34:07,544 --> 00:34:10,480
- I ate at the bar.
I'm a regular there.

451
00:34:10,513 --> 00:34:12,983
- Can anyone corroborate
your story?

452
00:34:13,016 --> 00:34:14,884
- I'm sure the bartender can.

453
00:34:14,918 --> 00:34:16,386
- You got a name for me?

454
00:34:16,419 --> 00:34:19,456
- I can't remember who
was working that night.

455
00:34:19,489 --> 00:34:21,057
I think it was Meagan.

456
00:34:22,158 --> 00:34:25,328
- Can you at least tell me
what this is all about?

457
00:34:25,362 --> 00:34:28,598
- Amelia Davis. She was
attacked last Wednesday night.

458
00:34:28,632 --> 00:34:30,533
- My God!
Is she all right?

459
00:34:33,436 --> 00:34:35,538
You think it was me.

460
00:34:35,572 --> 00:34:38,908
- Just asking questions,
Mr. Rossi.

461
00:34:40,810 --> 00:34:42,512
I'll be in touch.

462
00:34:53,957 --> 00:34:56,559
Meagan, I gotta ask you
a few questions.

463
00:34:56,593 --> 00:34:59,696
Were you working here
last Wednesday night?

464
00:34:59,729 --> 00:35:01,031
- Wednesday's my night off.

465
00:35:01,064 --> 00:35:03,433
The manager saves me
for the weekends.

466
00:35:03,466 --> 00:35:05,468
- So who was working?

467
00:35:05,502 --> 00:35:07,871
- Dave. He's the manager.

468
00:35:09,439 --> 00:35:13,343
- I'm trying to get some
information on this individual.

469
00:35:14,144 --> 00:35:15,645
- Carlo.

470
00:35:15,679 --> 00:35:17,080
- How well
do you know him?

471
00:35:17,113 --> 00:35:21,418
- Enough to tell you his name.
What's this about?

472
00:35:21,451 --> 00:35:24,387
- I'm conducting
a criminal investigation.

473
00:35:25,755 --> 00:35:28,591
- He's in here
a couple of times a week.

474
00:35:28,625 --> 00:35:30,727
- Does he pay cash,
credit card?

475
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:32,996
- Credit card.
Every time.

476
00:35:33,029 --> 00:35:36,700
- I'm gonna need to see your
receipts from Wednesday night.

477
00:35:36,733 --> 00:35:40,136
- I only swipe the card.
Dave takes care of the rest.

478
00:35:40,170 --> 00:35:41,771
He's in at 6:00.

479
00:35:43,039 --> 00:35:46,609
- Well then, you get Dave
to give me a call, OK?

480
00:35:46,643 --> 00:35:48,445
- Will do.

481
00:35:49,913 --> 00:35:52,982
- We wanna brand Amelia
as the next Oprah...

482
00:35:54,150 --> 00:35:56,986
uniting and inspiring
women of all kinds.

483
00:35:57,020 --> 00:36:01,758
Your words will comfort them.
Your message will empower them.

484
00:36:01,791 --> 00:36:04,994
They can read the blog
from the workplace...

485
00:36:08,498 --> 00:36:10,633
keep your book
next to their bed,

486
00:36:10,667 --> 00:36:12,702
listen to your podcast
on their iPod and,

487
00:36:12,736 --> 00:36:14,971
if things progress
as we expect,

488
00:36:15,004 --> 00:36:17,874
they'll soon be
watching your TV show.

489
00:36:20,009 --> 00:36:22,779
Never Back Down
will
be the place women go

490
00:36:22,812 --> 00:36:26,649
when they feel threatened or
feel like they've lost control.

491
00:36:26,683 --> 00:36:30,019
You will help them get back
to who they were.

492
00:36:42,532 --> 00:36:45,502
- Look, I get your personal
interest in this case.

493
00:36:45,535 --> 00:36:47,070
But like I told you
over the phone,

494
00:36:47,103 --> 00:36:49,205
I don't see anything
unusual with...

495
00:36:49,239 --> 00:36:51,908
- Devine.
Darryl Devine.

496
00:36:56,513 --> 00:36:58,081
- Devine.
Thank you.

497
00:36:59,182 --> 00:37:03,052
- Look, Amelia Davis was
attacked in her home,

498
00:37:03,086 --> 00:37:04,921
and Devine is
our prime suspect.

499
00:37:04,954 --> 00:37:06,656
You wouldn't be
breaking any rules.

500
00:37:06,689 --> 00:37:09,826
I just want the same information
you have. That's all.

501
00:37:09,859 --> 00:37:12,028
- What day are
you looking at?

502
00:37:12,061 --> 00:37:15,532
- For starters,
Wednesday the 7th.

503
00:37:22,906 --> 00:37:25,575
