00:56:18,407 --> 00:56:20,776
- That's ridiculous!

759
00:56:20,809 --> 00:56:22,110
- That's our offer.

760
00:56:22,144 --> 00:56:24,846
Considering the circumstances,
I would suggest

761
00:56:24,880 --> 00:56:26,848
your client seriously
think about it.

762
00:56:26,882 --> 00:56:29,217
- Circumstances?
You have to be kidding me.

763
00:56:29,251 --> 00:56:30,719
You barely have a case.

764
00:56:32,988 --> 00:56:34,389
We'll see you in court.

765
00:56:34,423 --> 00:56:36,291
- Suit yourself.

766
00:56:38,160 --> 00:56:41,997
I'm sure a jury will find
Ms. Davis' choice of company...

767
00:56:43,432 --> 00:56:45,300
quite interesting.

768
00:56:49,037 --> 00:56:51,940
This has to be a mistake.

769
00:56:51,974 --> 00:56:53,742
- The mugshot
looks real to me.

770
00:56:53,775 --> 00:56:57,112
I just don't know the specifics
of the crime yet. That's all.

771
00:56:57,145 --> 00:56:58,814
- You said he had
a clean record.

772
00:56:58,847 --> 00:57:01,717
- Well, nothing came up
on my database.

773
00:57:01,750 --> 00:57:04,252
So I put a call in
to my FBI contact,

774
00:57:04,286 --> 00:57:06,288
asked him to
look into Interpol.

775
00:57:06,321 --> 00:57:07,923
And this is
what he found.

776
00:57:08,924 --> 00:57:11,693
- I finally meet
someone I like.

777
00:57:11,727 --> 00:57:13,762
- Have you spoken
to him again yet?

778
00:57:13,795 --> 00:57:16,331
- No. I cancelled
our date for tonight.

779
00:57:16,365 --> 00:57:19,134
- Good. I want you to
stay away from him

780
00:57:19,167 --> 00:57:21,370
until we know exactly
what he's hiding.

781
00:57:22,804 --> 00:57:25,107
- What about Darryl?

782
00:57:25,140 --> 00:57:28,710
- The hotel's sending
tapes in this afternoon.

783
00:57:28,744 --> 00:57:32,247
They had 15 active security
cameras working that day,

784
00:57:32,280 --> 00:57:34,783
so I've assigned 2 guys
to go through them.

785
00:57:34,816 --> 00:57:37,986
As soon as I find something,
Amelia, I'll give you a call.

786
00:57:39,388 --> 00:57:42,324
- OK. Thanks.

787
00:57:42,357 --> 00:57:43,692
- Yeah.

788
00:59:25,927 --> 00:59:28,029
Amelia, what were
you thinking?

789
00:59:28,063 --> 00:59:29,264
- I know it was stupid.

790
00:59:29,297 --> 00:59:31,433
- You're just lucky
they didn't see you.

791
00:59:31,466 --> 00:59:34,035
- Well, at least
I know the truth.

792
00:59:34,069 --> 00:59:35,871
- Yeah, well, there's more.

793
00:59:35,904 --> 00:59:38,874
'Cause while you were out
playing private eye,

794
00:59:38,907 --> 00:59:41,243
I got a call from
my contact in Italy.

795
00:59:41,276 --> 00:59:44,446
Carlo Rossi
has no arrest record.

796
00:59:44,479 --> 00:59:47,015
But under the name
of Carlo Mancini,

797
00:59:47,048 --> 00:59:51,386
he was arrested on 4 accounts of
fraud and extortion 4 years ago.

798
00:59:51,419 --> 00:59:53,188
All charges were dropped.

799
00:59:54,189 --> 00:59:55,290
- How come?

800
00:59:55,323 --> 00:59:56,992
- Well, as it turns out,

801
00:59:57,025 --> 01:00:00,395
Carlo's family owns some
major real estate in Naples.

802
01:00:01,563 --> 01:00:04,065
They have a lot
of influence out there.

803
01:00:04,099 --> 01:00:05,000
The guy I spoke to

804
01:00:05,033 --> 01:00:07,602
didn't even wanna talk
about it on the phone.

805
01:00:07,636 --> 01:00:10,338
So I'm gonna be calling
the investigating officer

806
01:00:10,372 --> 01:00:12,541
later tonight to get
some more information.

807
01:00:12,574 --> 01:00:15,210
I even put a call in
to Homeland Security

808
01:00:15,243 --> 01:00:18,013
to find out the condition
of his work visa.

809
01:00:19,247 --> 01:00:21,516
- God, I feel so stupid!

810
01:00:22,517 --> 01:00:23,718
- It wasn't your fault.

811
01:00:23,752 --> 01:00:27,522
- He and Darryl must've been
planning this the whole time.

812
01:00:29,057 --> 01:00:31,159
- Look, you just
gotta promise me

813
01:00:31,193 --> 01:00:33,328
that you'll stay
far away from this guy, OK?

814
01:00:33,361 --> 01:00:35,363
Until after we sort
this whole thing out.

815
01:00:35,397 --> 01:00:37,966
I have the paperwork for
a restraining order for you.

816
01:00:37,999 --> 01:00:42,270
- You know what works better
than a restraining order? A gun.

817
01:00:43,605 --> 01:00:46,541
- Look, Amelia, you have
to understand that a gun

818
01:00:46,575 --> 01:00:49,578
is not a way of reclaiming
power or striking back.

819
01:00:49,611 --> 01:00:52,347
I mean, a gun's a means
of defending yourself

820
01:00:52,380 --> 01:00:54,583
when there's
no other alternative.

821
01:00:54,616 --> 01:00:56,184
You understand that?

822
01:00:56,218 --> 01:00:59,087
- I don't wanna rely on
some judge to protect me.

823
01:00:59,120 --> 01:01:01,923
Now that I know who it is,
I can protect myself.

824
01:01:41,029 --> 01:01:46,001
It's impossible to feel safe
and protected all the time.

825
01:01:46,034 --> 01:01:48,536
In one way or another,
we are all vulnerable.

826
01:01:54,542 --> 01:01:57,712
Those that we let in know
where we hurt the most,

827
01:01:57,746 --> 01:02:00,949
our worst fears,
our insecurities.

828
01:02:02,317 --> 01:02:05,053
Hi, I'm not here to take
your call right now.

829
01:02:05,086 --> 01:02:06,488
Please leave me a message.

830
01:02:12,227 --> 01:02:14,462
Those who want
to get in but can't

831
01:02:14,496 --> 01:02:16,431
look for cracks
in our armour.

832
01:02:21,770 --> 01:02:25,173
- But is your investigation
on Carlo Mancini...

833
01:02:25,206 --> 01:02:26,474
Is it still ongoing?

834
01:02:28,710 --> 01:02:33,081
Yes. Yes, I would appreciate
receiving a copy of the file.

835
01:02:34,482 --> 01:02:38,053
-But it is how we deal
with our vulnerabilities

836
01:02:38,086 --> 01:02:42,023
that we define our strengths
and our weaknesses.

837
01:02:42,057 --> 01:02:44,459
And while I know
I can't change the past,

838
01:02:44,492 --> 01:02:47,395
I believe that being a victim
is a state of mind.

839
01:02:48,663 --> 01:02:51,299
I am going to change
my state of mind.

840
01:03:00,642 --> 01:03:03,378
"Never back down"
is only the beginning.

841
01:03:03,411 --> 01:03:05,647
The end is when
we are confident,

842
01:03:05,680 --> 01:03:09,584
secure in who we are,
able to defend ourselves.

843
01:03:13,521 --> 01:03:16,124
Defamation of character?

844
01:03:16,157 --> 01:03:19,594
Intentional infliction
of emotional distress?

845
01:03:19,627 --> 01:03:21,629
This is all lies!

846
01:03:21,663 --> 01:03:24,666
- From a legal standpoint,
they're gonna lose.

847
01:03:24,699 --> 01:03:27,369
But I've been up
against Lana Grey before,

848
01:03:27,402 --> 01:03:29,270
and she'll take this
to the end

849
01:03:29,304 --> 01:03:31,139
just to keep seeing
herself on TV.

850
01:03:32,173 --> 01:03:34,309
Pictures of you
with a convict

851
01:03:34,342 --> 01:03:35,543
won't go over well

852
01:03:35,577 --> 01:03:38,680
with your audience or
with the advertisers,

853
01:03:38,713 --> 01:03:40,515
even if this was
all a setup.

854
01:03:41,850 --> 01:03:44,285
- This is
my private life.

855
01:03:44,319 --> 01:03:46,621
I didn't do
anything wrong.

856
01:03:46,654 --> 01:03:50,525
- No, but that doesn't matter
in the court of public opinion.

857
01:03:50,558 --> 01:03:55,230
If you lose your credibility,
you lose everything.

858
01:03:56,331 --> 01:04:00,402
Modern Media Works is willing
to pay all the money

859
01:04:00,435 --> 01:04:02,337
for this
to go away quietly.

860
01:04:03,338 --> 01:04:04,773
It won't cost
you a thing.

861
01:04:04,806 --> 01:04:06,307
- Yes, it will.

862
01:04:06,341 --> 01:04:09,511
I'm tired of being
pushed around.

863
01:04:33,902 --> 01:04:35,437
-My papers are in order.

864
01:04:35,470 --> 01:04:37,839
I still don't know
what you want from me.

865
01:04:37,872 --> 01:04:39,908
- It says here
you're a lying thief

866
01:04:39,941 --> 01:04:42,277
who extorts grieving
women for money.

867
01:04:42,310 --> 01:04:44,345
- This is out of
your jurisdiction.

868
01:04:44,379 --> 01:04:46,748
And all those charges
against me were dismissed.

869
01:04:47,749 --> 01:04:48,683
- Tell me something.

870
01:04:48,716 --> 01:04:51,152
What's your involvement
with Darryl Devine?

871
01:04:51,186 --> 01:04:53,588
- I'm not talking
without my lawyer.

872
01:04:53,621 --> 01:04:56,458
- 'Cause you 2 guys seem
to have a lot in common.

873
01:04:56,491 --> 01:04:57,759
You know what I think?

874
01:04:57,792 --> 01:05:01,262
I think you read about
Ms. Davis' upcoming payday

875
01:05:01,296 --> 01:05:03,765
and you thought to yourself:
"Easy score."

876
01:05:03,798 --> 01:05:05,900
- That's a lie.

877
01:05:05,934 --> 01:05:10,638
- We know all about
your family back in Italy.

878
01:05:10,672 --> 01:05:13,241
Portfolio's not
what it used to be, is it?

879
01:05:14,275 --> 01:05:15,777
So what have
we got so far?

880
01:05:15,810 --> 01:05:20,281
You've got a history of taking
advantage of women for money.

881
01:05:20,315 --> 01:05:22,917
You conveniently
pop up out of nowhere

882
01:05:22,951 --> 01:05:25,386
just when Miss Davis
is about to sell her blog.

883
01:05:25,420 --> 01:05:27,755
You've been seen associating
with her ex-husband

884
01:05:27,789 --> 01:05:29,924
who just so happens to
be suing her right now

885
01:05:29,958 --> 01:05:31,392
and using you
for leverage.

886
01:05:31,426 --> 01:05:33,862
I mean, that's a pretty
tight fit isn't it?

887
01:05:33,895 --> 01:05:36,631
One phone call to immigration

888
01:05:36,664 --> 01:05:39,901
about a potential
extortion on US soil

889
01:05:39,934 --> 01:05:42,370
and neither Carlo Rossi
or Carlo Mancini

890
01:05:42,403 --> 01:05:45,507
will ever set foot in this
country again, you got that?

891
01:05:45,540 --> 01:05:48,610
- Federal crimes,
out of your jurisdiction.

892
01:05:48,643 --> 01:05:50,612
- Jurisdiction.
Yeah, I know.

893
01:05:50,645 --> 01:05:53,548
I know, I know.
You keep reminding me.

894
01:05:53,581 --> 01:05:56,784
For an innocent man, you sure
seem to know an awful lot

895
01:05:56,818 --> 01:05:58,786
about the judicial system.

896
01:05:58,820 --> 01:06:01,856
- I came to this country
to start over again.

897
01:06:02,790 --> 01:06:05,260
That's why
I changed my name.

898
01:06:05,293 --> 01:06:07,262
It has nothing
to do with you.

899
01:06:07,295 --> 01:06:08,663
- And that's
where you're wrong.

900
01:06:08,696 --> 01:06:10,932
Because when it comes
to Miss Davis' security,

901
01:06:10,965 --> 01:06:12,567
it has everything
to do with me.

902
01:06:12,600 --> 01:06:14,836
-I was trying
to protect her!

903
01:06:14,869 --> 01:06:16,838
- How?

904
01:06:16,871 --> 01:06:20,575
By plotting with her abusive
ex-husband to extort her?

905
01:06:20,608 --> 01:06:23,311
-I tried to
pay him off, all right?

906
01:06:23,344 --> 01:06:25,547
So he would
leave her alone.

907
01:06:26,581 --> 01:06:27,749
It's you, Wilson.

908
01:06:28,750 --> 01:06:30,752
You who can't protect her.

909
01:06:31,753 --> 01:06:33,955
She's in danger,

910
01:06:33,988 --> 01:06:36,758
and I'm trying
to keep her safe.

911
01:06:39,494 --> 01:06:42,397
- I'll be keeping
an eye on you, Carlo.

912
01:06:43,932 --> 01:06:46,901
- Isn't that
what you told Darryl?

913
01:06:53,641 --> 01:06:56,878
- It was like I was looking
at a complete stranger.

914
01:06:56,911 --> 01:06:58,746
- You couldn't have known.

915
01:06:58,780 --> 01:07:00,281
- But I should have.

916
01:07:00,315 --> 01:07:02,684
When things went bad
with Darryl,

917
01:07:02,717 --> 01:07:05,486
I was young, naive.

918
01:07:06,654 --> 01:07:08,556
Now I know what people
are capable of

919
01:07:08,590 --> 01:07:10,592
and I still opened
myself up to this.

920
01:07:10,625 --> 01:07:12,560
- So you took
a chance on someone.

921
01:07:14,762 --> 01:07:18,633
- I barely knew him.
I just can't trust anyone.

922
01:07:18,666 --> 01:07:21,069
- If you'd have shut
yourself off after Darryl,

923
01:07:21,102 --> 01:07:23,771
you never would've gotten
your life back on track.

924
01:07:23,805 --> 01:07:27,875
You never would've started the
blog. You never would've met me.

925
01:07:30,678 --> 01:07:31,879
- I know you're right.

926
01:07:33,615 --> 01:07:37,418
I'm just so frustrated that I've
allowed these guys to affect me.

927
01:07:38,419 --> 01:07:41,022
I'm tired of
feeling victimized.

928
01:07:42,056 --> 01:07:44,058
- What about
the lawsuit?

929
01:07:45,159 --> 01:07:48,029
- The thought of them
walking away with one cent

930
01:07:48,062 --> 01:07:49,063
makes me sick.

931
01:07:50,064 --> 01:07:51,599
- Whose decision is it?

932
01:07:51,633 --> 01:07:52,967
- Mine.

933
01:07:54,569 --> 01:07:57,672
But Modern Media Works
can terminate my contract.

934
01:07:57,705 --> 01:07:59,540
- Well, that won't happen.

935
01:08:00,675 --> 01:08:03,378
- At this point, I don't
care about the job

936
01:08:03,411 --> 01:08:04,779
or the blog
or the money.

937
01:08:04,812 --> 01:08:08,316
Darryl and Carlo think
that they can exploit me.

938
01:08:13,821 --> 01:08:16,524
- Is there
anything I can do?

939
01:08:19,994 --> 01:08:22,096
- Can you stay over tonight?

940
01:08:22,130 --> 01:08:24,332
- Of course.

941
01:08:36,811 --> 01:08:38,713
- This is early
for you, Bernice.

942
01:08:38,746 --> 01:08:40,715
- Amelia, turn on the TV.

943
01:08:40,748 --> 01:08:42,417
-What channel?
- 97.

944
01:08:48,489 --> 01:08:50,458
- Look, I paid for my crimes.

945
01:08:50,491 --> 01:08:53,494
But this media pressure,
this hounding

946
01:08:53,528 --> 01:08:57,098
has--has caused extreme
emotional stress on me.

947
01:08:57,131 --> 01:08:58,332
- My God!

948
01:08:58,366 --> 01:09:02,437
-All this because of
Amelia Davis, media darling.

949
01:09:02,470 --> 01:09:05,006
What's excessive is the
vindictive and unjust way

950
01:09:05,039 --> 01:09:06,407
that I've been treated.

951
01:09:06,441 --> 01:09:07,809
It's not about the money.

952
01:09:07,842 --> 01:09:10,478
It's about justice
and doing what's right.

953
01:09:10,511 --> 01:09:13,448
-Please tell me
what happened.

954
01:09:14,916 --> 01:09:16,984
- What the hell
does this mean, Bernice?

955
01:09:18,019 --> 01:09:20,154
- Scare tactics.
But it worked.

956
01:09:20,188 --> 01:09:22,757
Modern Media Works
wants to settle.

957
01:09:22,790 --> 01:09:23,758
- No way.

958
01:09:24,926 --> 01:09:27,695
-Don't worry.
Grosslight has deep pockets.

959
01:09:27,729 --> 01:09:30,498
- I don't care. Let them
try to take this to court.

960
01:09:30,531 --> 01:09:31,899
Let them
release the photos.

961
01:09:31,933 --> 01:09:33,768
But I'm not
agreeing to anything.

962
01:09:33,801 --> 01:09:35,770
- OK. I'll call you
when I know more.

963
01:09:35,803 --> 01:09:36,804
- OK.

964
01:09:41,209 --> 01:09:45,646
- My God! I feel like my life
is completely out of my hands.

965
01:09:50,084 --> 01:09:51,986
Wilson called.

966
01:09:52,019 --> 01:09:55,523
He said that they caught Darryl
on the surveillance tapes.

967
01:09:55,556 --> 01:09:58,826
- That's fantastic!
When can they arrest him?

968
01:09:59,961 --> 01:10:02,196
- The DA needs to
sign off on the warrant.

969
01:10:02,230 --> 01:10:03,698
But it shouldn't be long.

970
01:10:05,500 --> 01:10:08,870
I really need to get out
of the city for a while.

971
01:10:11,706 --> 01:10:15,676
- What about that spa you sent
me to last year for my birthday?

972
01:10:17,712 --> 01:10:21,015
- Yeah, now you're talking.
That's exactly what I need.

973
01:10:21,048 --> 01:10:22,617
- What we need.

974
01:10:22,650 --> 01:10:24,685
- You'll go with me?

975
01:10:24,719 --> 01:10:27,622
- You don't think I'd let you
go anywhere alone, do you?

976
01:10:28,656 --> 01:10:30,458
- Thank you.

977
01:10:45,740 --> 01:10:48,009
I think somebody's
following us.

978
01:10:50,545 --> 01:10:52,914
- Probably just
a coincidence.

979
01:10:55,550 --> 01:10:57,084
- It's Carlo!

980
01:10:57,118 --> 01:10:58,953
- He's coming.

981
01:11:04,258 --> 01:11:05,827
- Pull over!

982
01:11:05,860 --> 01:11:07,528
- Leave me alone!

983
01:11:07,562 --> 01:11:09,597
- Pull over! I need
to talk to you.

984
01:11:22,009 --> 01:11:23,077
- Careful!

985
01:11:36,123 --> 01:11:39,594
- Amelia! Pick up
your cell phone!

986
01:11:44,665 --> 01:11:46,067
Amelia!

987
01:11:47,068 --> 01:11:48,302
- Leave me alone!

988
01:11:48,336 --> 01:11:50,671
- Pick up the phone!

989
01:12:25,239 --> 01:12:27,375
- How is he?

990
01:12:27,408 --> 01:12:29,277
- It doesn't look good.

991
01:12:29,310 --> 01:12:31,812
We had to let him go
after the interrogation.

992
01:12:31,846 --> 01:12:33,781
We didn't have enough
to hold him on.

993
01:12:34,815 --> 01:12:36,918
- I just wanna go home.

994
01:12:42,056 --> 01:12:45,026
- So anyway,
it was pretty interesting.

995
01:12:45,059 --> 01:12:46,027
There she is!

996
01:12:46,060 --> 01:12:47,762
She's coming back.

997
01:12:47,795 --> 01:12:48,996
Get her, get her.

998
01:12:51,299 --> 01:12:52,366
Here she comes.

999
01:12:52,400 --> 01:12:53,734
Ms. Davis, Ms. Davis!

1000
01:12:53,768 --> 01:12:56,170
What is your relationship
with Mr. Mancini?

1001
01:12:56,203 --> 01:12:57,972
Are you
romantically involved?

1002
01:12:58,005 --> 01:13:00,274
Amelia, have the police
laid any charges?

1003
01:13:00,308 --> 01:13:02,777
- She has no comment.
Leave her alone.

1004
01:13:02,810 --> 01:13:05,379
- Ms. Davis! Can you
make any comment?

1005
01:13:05,413 --> 01:13:06,781
- Amelia! Amelia!

1006
01:13:06,814 --> 01:13:08,950
Amelia,
one more question!

1007
01:13:18,392 --> 01:13:20,628
- I'll take the couch.

1008
01:13:41,215 --> 01:13:44,719
- This just came in.
You better take a look at it.

1009
01:13:48,155 --> 01:13:50,691
- No wonder they
didn't prosecute.

1010
01:13:50,725 --> 01:13:52,860
The whole case
was frivolous.

1011
01:13:52,893 --> 01:13:56,097
Seems like the women were the
ones trying to shake him down.

1012
01:13:56,130 --> 01:13:58,766
- Based on these bank
statements, I can see why.

1013
01:13:58,799 --> 01:14:00,401
- Yeah.

1014
01:14:00,434 --> 01:14:02,103
- But his money
won't help him now.

1015
01:14:02,136 --> 01:14:03,304
- Thanks.

1016
01:14:09,844 --> 01:14:11,212
-Hello?

1017
01:14:11,245 --> 01:14:14,148
- Amelia, I have
some news about Carlo.

1018
01:14:17,485 --> 01:14:20,121
- No questions,
but I have a statement.

1019
01:14:22,089 --> 01:14:25,326
I had a relationship with
Carlo Mancini that ended

1020
01:14:25,359 --> 01:14:27,962
because I chose
to believe information

1021
01:14:27,995 --> 01:14:29,897
that turned out
to be untrue.

1022
01:14:29,930 --> 01:14:33,300
I pray Carlo recovers and
that I will get the chance

1023
01:14:33,334 --> 01:14:35,002
to speak with him again,

1024
01:14:35,036 --> 01:14:37,138
to apologize
for doubting him.

1025
01:14:37,171 --> 01:14:40,341
But I will not apologize
to my ex-husband,

1026
01:14:40,374 --> 01:14:42,209
whose allegations
against me

1027
01:14:42,243 --> 01:14:45,079
are just another attempt
at intimidation.

1028
01:14:45,112 --> 01:14:48,482
Abuse disguises itself
in many forms.

1029
01:14:48,516 --> 01:14:51,152
It can be physical
or psychological.

1030
01:14:51,185 --> 01:14:54,789
It feeds on our insecurities
and aims to strip us

1031
01:14:54,822 --> 01:14:57,324
of our identity
and self-worth.

1032
01:14:57,358 --> 01:15:00,895
But I know who I am and
I know who you are, Darryl.

1033
01:15:00,928 --> 01:15:02,830
You are a selfish, arrogant,

1034
01:15:02,863 --> 01:15:05,066
pathetic excuse
for a human being.

1035
01:15:05,099 --> 01:15:08,035
And if you wanna up
your lawsuit for defamation

1036
01:15:08,069 --> 01:15:10,237
because I said that,
go right ahead.

1037
01:15:10,271 --> 01:15:13,274
Because no matter
what you threaten to do,

1038
01:15:13,307 --> 01:15:14,975
I will never back down.

1039
01:15:15,009 --> 01:15:16,477
Thank you.

1040
01:15:16,510 --> 01:15:18,479
- One question.
What about the lawsuit?

1041
01:15:18,512 --> 01:15:20,848
Are you in love
with him? Amelia!

1042
01:15:20,881 --> 01:15:22,183
- Amelia!
- Ms. Davis!

1043
01:15:26,420 --> 01:15:28,856
- I'm so proud of you.

1044
01:15:32,126 --> 01:15:33,527
- Thank you.

1045
01:15:43,237 --> 01:15:44,338
- What have you got?

1046
01:15:44,371 --> 01:15:46,907
- That warrant you
want for Darryl Devine?

1047
01:15:46,941 --> 01:15:48,409
- Yeah.
- DA just signed it.

1048
01:15:48,442 --> 01:15:52,346
- I want 4 uniforms at Darryl
Devine's place immediately.

1049
01:15:52,379 --> 01:15:53,347
- OK.

1050
01:15:53,380 --> 01:15:54,782
- Possible take down.

1051
01:15:56,584 --> 01:15:59,220
Police! Open up, Mr. Devine!

1052
01:16:17,605 --> 01:16:19,907
Yeah, it's me.
He's gone.

1053
01:16:19,940 --> 01:16:23,043
Put out an APB
on him and his truck.

1054
01:16:26,013 --> 01:16:30,084
- OK. Thanks, Hank.
I appreciate it.

1055
01:16:33,087 --> 01:16:35,055
Darryl's on the loose again.

1056
01:16:35,089 --> 01:16:37,458
- It never ends.

1057
01:16:37,491 --> 01:16:39,326
- You went out?

1058
01:16:39,360 --> 01:16:42,563
- Yeah, there's a horde
of reporters out there.

1059
01:16:42,596 --> 01:16:45,466
Your TV appearance
made everything worse.

1060
01:16:45,499 --> 01:16:49,136
- My God! This is
getting ridiculous.

1061
01:16:49,170 --> 01:16:52,173
- You're coming home with me.
- They're just gonna follow us.

1062
01:16:52,206 --> 01:16:54,441
- I'm ahead of you.
I put my car in the back.

1063
01:16:56,177 --> 01:16:58,579
- It can be physical
or psychological.

1064
01:16:58,612 --> 01:17:02,049
It feeds on our insecurities
and aims to strip us

1065
01:17:02,082 --> 01:17:04,151
of our identity
and self-worth.

1066
01:17:04,185 --> 01:17:07,488
But I know who I am and
I know who you are, Darryl.

1067
01:17:07,521 --> 01:17:10,124
You are a selfish, arrogant...

1068
01:17:11,659 --> 01:17:13,294
- ... excuse
for a human being.

1069
01:17:13,327 --> 01:17:14,195
- Bitch!

1070
01:17:14,228 --> 01:17:16,297
-If you wanna
up your lawsuit

1071
01:17:16,330 --> 01:17:18,465
because I said that,
go right ahead.

1072
01:17:18,499 --> 01:17:21,302
Because no matter
what you threaten to do,

1073
01:17:21,335 --> 01:17:24,004
I will never back down.
Thank you.

1074
01:17:39,653 --> 01:17:41,989
- Every time I try to relax...

1075
01:17:42,022 --> 01:17:43,123
- Who is it?

1076
01:17:44,158 --> 01:17:45,492
- It's Bernice.

1077
01:17:45,526 --> 01:17:46,660
- Voice mail.

1078
01:17:47,695 --> 01:17:50,197
- Bernice, what's up?

1079
01:17:50,231 --> 01:17:51,365
- After your TV performance,

1080
01:17:51,398 --> 01:17:53,934
the server went nuts
from all the traffic.

1081
01:17:53,968 --> 01:17:57,137
Shut the whole thing down.
It's back up again, though.

1082
01:17:57,171 --> 01:17:59,139
- Were the responses
good or bad?

1083
01:17:59,173 --> 01:18:02,009
- Your fans are
showering you with love.

1084
01:18:02,042 --> 01:18:04,511
- What about Darryl
and the lawsuit?

1085
01:18:04,545 --> 01:18:07,281
- Modern Media Works
is backing you 100%.

1086
01:18:07,314 --> 01:18:09,083
They don't want to settle.

1087
01:18:09,116 --> 01:18:10,951
Darryl is a footnote.

1088
01:18:10,985 --> 01:18:12,486
- That's fantastic!

1089
01:18:12,519 --> 01:18:14,088
- It gets better.

1090
01:18:14,121 --> 01:18:17,625
I've had 50 calls
for interview requests.

1091
01:18:17,658 --> 01:18:19,426
And I don't mean affiliates.

1092
01:18:19,460 --> 01:18:21,629
I'm talking the ones
that go by one name.

1093
01:18:21,662 --> 01:18:24,231
And Random House
wants the book rights.

1094
01:18:24,265 --> 01:18:25,399
- This is unbelievable!

1095
01:18:25,432 --> 01:18:28,302
- Call me in the morning.
We'll strategize.

1096
01:18:28,335 --> 01:18:30,170
- OK, thank you.

1097
01:18:30,204 --> 01:18:32,172
- So?

1098
01:18:32,206 --> 01:18:35,576
- Darryl is out of luck
on all fronts.

1099
01:18:35,609 --> 01:18:39,580
- Modern Media Works took its
settlement offer off the table?

1100
01:18:39,613 --> 01:18:40,714
- For good.

1101
01:18:40,748 --> 01:18:43,183
- Things are looking up
for you, girl.

1102
01:18:46,420 --> 01:18:49,056
- I feel like I wanna write
something on the blog.

1103
01:18:49,089 --> 01:18:51,292
Do you mind if I go upstairs?
- Sure.

1104
01:18:51,325 --> 01:18:53,193
- OK.

1105
01:18:56,230 --> 01:18:59,633
Every instance of abuse
has 2 victims.

1106
01:19:00,634 --> 01:19:02,503
The second is trust.

1107
01:19:04,038 --> 01:19:07,107
When the person you
trusted more than anyone

1108
01:19:07,141 --> 01:19:09,610
turns on you and
destroys that trust,

1109
01:19:09,643 --> 01:19:13,280
you think you will never
let anyone in ever again.

1110
01:19:18,252 --> 01:19:21,455
I've recently allowed myself
to have faith in someone.

1111
01:19:22,756 --> 01:19:25,125
For the first time
in a long time,

1112
01:19:25,159 --> 01:19:26,160
I can say...

1113
01:19:27,528 --> 01:19:30,531
"I have a friend
and I trust her."

1114
01:20:41,368 --> 01:20:42,803
- I need a beer.

1115
01:20:42,836 --> 01:20:45,305
- What the hell
do you think you're doing?

1116
01:20:45,339 --> 01:20:47,741
- The lawsuit is dead.

1117
01:20:50,711 --> 01:20:54,248
- Shhh! One more step
and you're dead.

1118
01:20:55,616 --> 01:20:57,251
- Put it down.

1119
01:20:57,284 --> 01:20:59,520
- You're not gonna
screw this up for me.

1120
01:20:59,553 --> 01:21:02,289
- For you? I thought
we were in this together.

1121
01:21:02,322 --> 01:21:04,591
We
were supposed
to get our sweet Amelia.

1122
01:21:04,625 --> 01:21:07,828
- We were. But then the
boyfriend got in the way.

1123
01:21:07,861 --> 01:21:09,730
- So what do we do now?

1124
01:21:09,763 --> 01:21:13,467
- Like you said,
the lawsuit's dead.

1125
01:21:13,500 --> 01:21:15,102
So are you.

1126
01:21:48,335 --> 01:21:51,772
"Dear Amelia: Your words
have given me courage.

1127
01:21:51,805 --> 01:21:54,775
"She has
pushed me around too long.

1128
01:21:54,808 --> 01:21:56,243
"I was embarrassed...

1129
01:21:56,276 --> 01:21:58,912
"Because my abuser is my wife.

1130
01:22:00,814 --> 01:22:02,816
"But tonight...

1131
01:22:03,750 --> 01:22:06,153
"I stand up for myself.

1132
01:22:07,421 --> 01:22:09,823
"Tonight, I tell her
that it is over.

1133
01:22:09,857 --> 01:22:11,792
"I am leaving
her for good.

1134
01:22:13,560 --> 01:22:16,763
"Thanks for guiding me
through the hurt.

1135
01:22:16,797 --> 01:22:18,832
"Trevor."

1136
01:22:30,244 --> 01:22:33,714
- Hey, what are you doing?
I thought you were working.

1137
01:22:35,849 --> 01:22:38,185
- It was all
a lie, wasn't it?

1138
01:22:38,986 --> 01:22:41,788
You were never
Embarrassed. Trevor was.

1139
01:22:41,822 --> 01:22:44,358
- He certainly was
an embarrassment.

1140
01:22:44,391 --> 01:22:46,426
- You were
the one abusing him.

1141
01:22:46,460 --> 01:22:49,796
- I knew I should've thrown
this away. I just couldn't.

1142
01:22:49,830 --> 01:22:53,834
- Everything that you've
ever told me was a lie.

1143
01:22:54,868 --> 01:22:57,604
- Talk about the pot
calling the kettle.

1144
01:23:02,009 --> 01:23:04,444
Your entire life
is a concoction.

1145
01:23:04,478 --> 01:23:05,445
- Wait.

1146
01:23:05,479 --> 01:23:07,381
- You're not a hero.

1147
01:23:07,414 --> 01:23:10,317
You're a coward who hides behind
her keyboard and a mouse.

1148
01:23:10,350 --> 01:23:12,386
- My God!

1149
01:23:12,419 --> 01:23:14,555
- You let Darryl
push you around?

1150
01:23:14,588 --> 01:23:17,724
-You
should've
done that years ago.

1151
01:23:17,758 --> 01:23:19,927
- I'm not a killer.

1152
01:23:19,960 --> 01:23:21,995
- No, you're not.
You're a victim.

1153
01:23:23,697 --> 01:23:25,699
- I trusted you.

1154
01:23:25,732 --> 01:23:28,535
- You are also a very bad
judge of character.

1155
01:23:28,569 --> 01:23:31,238
- What did I ever do to you?

1156
01:23:32,906 --> 01:23:35,008
- You ruined my life.

1157
01:23:37,044 --> 01:23:39,479
So I pushed
Trevor around a little.

1158
01:23:40,480 --> 01:23:43,750
It worked for us.
We were happy.

1159
01:23:46,053 --> 01:23:49,590
And then he started
reading your garbage.

1160
01:23:49,623 --> 01:23:51,525
"Never back down."

1161
01:23:52,893 --> 01:23:54,861
What a joke!

1162
01:23:55,862 --> 01:23:57,831
Got him all fired up.

1163
01:24:05,072 --> 01:24:06,773
- What are you doing?

1164
01:24:11,478 --> 01:24:14,381
- So you believe
that garbage?

1165
01:24:14,414 --> 01:24:15,782
- Yes.

1166
01:24:17,084 --> 01:24:18,619
This is it.

1167
01:24:18,652 --> 01:24:20,520
This, this is it.
We're through.

1168
01:24:20,554 --> 01:24:22,856
- So this is it.
This is your big stand.

1169
01:24:22,889 --> 01:24:25,025
You don't have the balls
to fight back?

1170
01:24:25,058 --> 01:24:27,494
- You don't know
what I'm capable of.

1171
01:24:29,062 --> 01:24:31,365
- Unfortunately, Trevor,

1172
01:24:31,398 --> 01:24:34,401
I know exactly what
you're capable of.

1173
01:24:38,972 --> 01:24:40,974
Put it down, Trevor.

1174
01:24:52,819 --> 01:24:54,521
I didn't have a choice.

1175
01:24:54,554 --> 01:24:57,524
Thanks to you, the police
assumed I was the victim.

1176
01:24:57,557 --> 01:24:59,493
I just had to show
them the letters.

1177
01:24:59,526 --> 01:25:00,494
Except this one.

1178
01:25:00,527 --> 01:25:02,562
So when you
think about it,

1179
01:25:02,596 --> 01:25:04,698
it's your fault
Trevor died.

1180
01:25:04,731 --> 01:25:06,433
- You're sick!

1181
01:25:06,466 --> 01:25:07,601
- Yeah.

1182
01:25:08,602 --> 01:25:09,836
The funny part is

1183
01:25:09,870 --> 01:25:12,706
Darryl's the one who
cared about the money.

1184
01:25:12,739 --> 01:25:14,708
I didn't care
about the money.

1185
01:25:14,741 --> 01:25:16,977
I just wanted
to make you suffer.

1186
01:25:18,979 --> 01:25:21,715
And then you gave me
the writing job.

1187
01:25:22,883 --> 01:25:26,620
And now I'm going to have
everything that you have.

1188
01:25:26,653 --> 01:25:28,422
When you think about it,

1189
01:25:28,455 --> 01:25:31,725
that is the sweetest
kind of revenge.

1190
01:25:31,758 --> 01:25:33,527
- You'll never
get away with this.

1191
01:25:33,560 --> 01:25:35,128
- You are
so wrong, sweetheart.

1192
01:25:35,162 --> 01:25:37,864
When the world finds out
that I killed Darryl

1193
01:25:37,898 --> 01:25:40,000
in an attempt
to protect you,

1194
01:25:40,033 --> 01:25:43,737
Modern Media Works is gonna
pass the torch on to me.

1195
01:25:43,770 --> 01:25:46,406
And I will continue
to lead the fight

1196
01:25:46,440 --> 01:25:50,944
on behalf of our fallen
martyr, Amelia Davis.

1197
01:26:12,566 --> 01:26:14,568
- I wish I'd gotten
to you earlier.

1198
01:26:15,836 --> 01:26:17,938
Luckily, you called me
when you did.

1199
01:26:18,939 --> 01:26:20,774
- I don't feel lucky.

1200
01:26:20,807 --> 01:26:22,509
- This isn't your fault.

1201
01:26:22,542 --> 01:26:25,746
There was no choice.
It was either you or her.

1202
01:26:28,181 --> 01:26:30,117
I've got some good news.

1203
01:26:30,150 --> 01:26:33,653
Carlo woke up.
He's gonna be OK.

1204
01:26:34,688 --> 01:26:36,823
He was asking about you.

1205
01:26:44,197 --> 01:26:47,134
Here comes the press.
We better get you home.

1206
01:26:49,703 --> 01:26:52,105
No more vehicles

1207
01:26:52,139 --> 01:26:54,107
on the parade route for today.

1208
01:27:02,048 --> 01:27:04,084
- You take care
of yourself, Amelia.

1209
01:27:04,117 --> 01:27:06,720
- I'm gonna be OK, Hank.

1210
01:27:39,085 --> 01:27:42,022
Closed captions:
Vision Globale

										
 


 

  
  
   
 

  
  
   
										